{"key":"processedPost-16115373","value":{"id":16115373,"first":16113829,"last":16116288,"when":1334930754,"utime":"04/20/12 05:05 PM","cleanedPost":"I've long recommended running a PC at 14 psi so it doesn't run dry.&nbsp; If you keep the stove setting too high, not only does it make a horrible racket, but it dries out the substrate in your jars, and will boil out the water in the pressure cooker too.<br />The important thing is to keep the weight/rocker off the nozzle until steam has escaped for ten minutes or so at the start of the cycle.&nbsp; This replaces all the air in the PC with steam, which is critical.<br />RR"}}